        "intro": "If your parent struggles to afford Medicare premiums, deductibles, or prescription drugs, Oklahoma's Medicare Savings Program can eliminate these costs entirely. The program has four tiers — the lowest tier (QMB) covers all Medicare premiums, deductibles, and coinsurance, while higher tiers cover at least Medicare Part B premiums. All tiers also provide Extra Help for prescription drugs, capping costs at $12.65 per medication in 2026.\n\nTypical savings run around $185 monthly, though this varies by tier and your parent's Medicare usage. Because Oklahoma has strict asset limits (around $2,000 for individuals, $3,000 for couples in lower tiers), this program works best for parents with limited savings but whose income falls just above Medicaid limits.",
